<paragraph id="8BB6C433FF87B606C4D5C80F2AA2FCC6" blockId="3.[151,1436,1284,1417]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="B97D1821FF87B606C4D5C80F2F78FC52" bold="true" box="[199,330,1284,1309]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Bionomics.</emphasis>
All specimens of the 
<typeStatus id="54B27A91FF87B606C656C80E2C46FC52" box="[580,628,1285,1309]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">type</typeStatus>
series were collected with a Malaise trap in an arid zone dominated by 
<taxonomicName id="4C09BFB0FF87B606C485C8222F20FC0E" box="[151,274,1321,1345]" class="Liliopsida" family="Agavaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="family">Agavaceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C09BFB0FF87B606C55AC8222F8FFC0E" box="[328,445,1321,1345]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Cactaceae</taxonomicName>
. The higher number of specimens was collected during the months of April and May. 
<emphasis id="B97D1821FF87B606C4D5C8472F7FFC2A" bold="true" box="[199,333,1356,1381]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after our friend and colleague Dr. Dalton de Souza Amorim, for his outstanding contribution to the systematics and phylogeny of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C09BFB0FF87B606C761C87B2DCBFCC6" box="[883,1017,1392,1417]" class="Insecta" family="Scatopsidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Scatopsidae</taxonomicName>
of the world.
</paragraph>
